channel.title: [PI] Server suddenly not running [Eclipse]
channel.description:
Hello guys, I have an issue as of recently... Suddenly, I can't run my server on "Eclipse" anymore. I'm getting an error and here it is. [CODE] Exception in thread "main" java.lang.Error: Unresolved compilation problems: IoAcceptor cannot be resolved to a type SocketAcceptor cannot be resolved to a type SocketAcceptorConfig cannot be resolved to a type SocketAcceptorConfig cannot be resolved to a type IoAcceptor cannot be resolved to a type
at game.Server.main(Server.java:140) [/CODE]
Any and every help is greatly appreciated.

item.title: [PI] Server suddenly not running [Eclipse]
item.dc:creator: @malimt malimt
item.description:
@malimt wrote:

[quote=“HeroicEmpire, post:2, topic:551603”]Its because the version of java that you are compiling with and then running with is different.

Right click on your project -> properties -> Java Compiler -> Compiler Compliance level

Now check your java run configurations for which jre you are using.[/quote]
Thank you very much.
